### evaluateSymbolicAdd() {#afa1844c524c0ee91d2cca0f3eac95382}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static bool evaluateSymbolicAdd (<a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcassembler">MCAssembler</a> &#42; Asm, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/namespaces/llvm/#ac66fe51a73cdf1ab9f07ca6ead1652e7">SectionAddrMap</a> &#42; Addrs, bool InSet, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcvalue">MCValue</a> &amp; LHS, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/aarch64/aarch64promoteconstant-cpp/#a90f8350fecae261c25be85d38b451bff">const</a> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcvalue">MCValue</a> &amp; RHS, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcvalue">MCValue</a> &amp; Res)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
Evaluate the result of an add between (conceptually) two MCValues.

This routine conceptually attempts to construct an <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcvalue">MCValue</a>: Result = (Result&#95;A - Result&#95;B + Result&#95;Cst) from two <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcvalue">MCValue</a>&#39;s LHS and RHS where Result = LHS + RHS and Result = (LHS&#95;A - LHS&#95;B + LHS&#95;Cst) + (RHS&#95;A - RHS&#95;B + RHS&#95;Cst).

This routine attempts to aggressively fold the operands such that the result is representable in an <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcvalue">MCValue</a>, but may not always succeed.


<SectionUser title="Returns">
True on success, false if the result is not representable in an <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mcvalue">MCValue</a>. NOTE: It is really important to have both the Asm and Layout arguments. They might look redundant, but this function can be used before layout is done (see the object streamer for example) and having the Asm argument lets us avoid relaxations early.
</SectionUser>

Definition at line <a href="#l00764">764</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/mc/mcexpr-cpp">MCExpr.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

</SectionDefinition>
